\begin{abstract}
We analytically describe the strong-field light-electron interaction using a quantized coherent laser state with arbitrary photon number, obtaining a light-electron wave function which is a closed-form solution of the time-dependent Schr\"odinger equation. This wave function provides information about the quantum optical features of the interaction not accessible by semi-classical theories. With this approach we can reveal the quantum optical properties of high-harmonic generation in gases by measuring the photon statistics of the transmitted laser radiation, leading to novel experiments in high-resolution XUV spectroscopy and attosecond science.
\end{abstract}
